// create spark dataframe of all emily tables
val mainDF = spark.read.parquet(sessionPaths(0))
val appsDF = spark.read.parquet(sessionPaths(1))
val impDF = spark.read.parquet(sessionPaths(2))
val selDF = spark.read.parquet(sessionPaths(3))
val adDF = spark.read.parquet(sessionPaths(4))
val mdDF = spark.read.parquet(sessionPaths(5))

//Agg count of transaction id's and removing the TR who repeated more than or equal to twice

val grpMain = mainDF.groupBy("transactionId").agg(count(lit(1)).as("main_tr_count"))
val validMain = grpMain.filter($"main_tr_count" ===1).drop($"main_tr_count").distinct()

val grpApps=appsDF.groupBy("transactionId").agg(count(lit(1)).as("main_tr_count"))
val validApps = grpApps.filter($"main_tr_count" ===1).drop($"main_tr_count").distinct()

val grpImp=impDF.groupBy("transactionId").agg(count(lit(1)).as("main_tr_count"))
val validImp = grpImp.filter($"main_tr_count" ===1).drop($"main_tr_count").distinct()

val grpSel=selDF.groupBy("transactionId").agg(count(lit(1)).as("main_tr_count"))
val validSel = grpSel.filter($"main_tr_count" ===1).drop($"main_tr_count").distinct()

val grpAd=adDF.groupBy("transactionId").agg(count(lit(1)).as("main_tr_count"))
val validAd = grpAd.filter($"main_tr_count" ===1).drop($"main_tr_count").distinct()

val grpMd = mdDF.groupBy("transactionId").agg(count(lit(1)).as("main_tr_count"))
val validMd = grpMd.filter($"main_tr_count" ===1).drop($"main_tr_count").distinct()
